" href="http://webdevstudios.com/2014/01/22/brian-messenlehner-is-speaking-at-wordcamp-norway-2014/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Melissa Hoppe";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2337:"<p>Brian is taking a trip across the ocean to speak at <a href="http://2014.norway.wordcamp.org/">WordCamp Norway</a> this year! <a href="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Screenshot_on_1.22.2014_at_10.57.00_AM.png"><img class="alignright size-full wp-image-8022" alt="Screenshot_on_1.22.2014_at_10.57.00_AM" src="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Screenshot_on_1.22.2014_at_10.57.00_AM.png" width="315" height="204" /></a>WordCamp Norway is being held at the <a title="Radisson Blu Hotel Nydalen, Oslo" href="http://www.radissonblu.no/hotellnydalen-oslo" target="_blank">Radisson Blu Hotel Nydalen, Oslo</a>. The event will run from the 25th to the 26th of January. You can view the entire schedule of WordCamp Norway on their <a href="http://2014.norway.wordcamp.org/schedule/">website</a>.</p>\n<p>Brian is speaking at <strong>15:20 CET on Saturday, January 25th in Room 1</strong>. He will be teaching you all about <span style="text-decoration: underline">Building Web Apps with WordPress. </span></p>\n<p><strong>Description:</strong></p>\n<p><em>WordPress started out as a blogging platform, but throughout the past 10 years, it has become so much more. It doesn&#8217;t matter if you&#8217;re new to the WordPress world, or if you have years of experience under your belt; with WordPress, you can make the impossible, possible. Brian will go through how to build and secure applications at a rapid pace, along with tips on how to save time and money while doing so. You will also get the opportunity to see some awesome apps and examples of things you can do with WordPress while drawing outside of the lines.</em></p>\n<p><em>Brian will also be speaking about <a href="http://apppresser.com/">AppPresser</a> &#8212; The first plugin framework that allows you to create native apps for iOS and/or Android using WordPress. He will illustrate how using AppPresser to create apps is just as easy as creating and customizing a WordPress website.</em></p>\n<p>If you don&#8217;t get the opportunity to speak with Brian during WordCamp hours, you can catch him at the after party which is being held at the venue itself in the Radisson hotel bar. As always, Brian is excited to reconnect with those of you he&#8217;s already met, and to connect for the first time with those of you he hasn&#8217;t!</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:96:"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/01/22/brian-messenlehner-is-speaking-at-wordcamp-norway-2014/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:57:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:28:"WDS at WordCamp Phoenix 2014";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:65:"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/01/15/wds-at-wordcamp-phoenix-2014/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:74:"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/01/15/wds-at-wordcamp-phoenix-2014/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 15 Jan 2014 15:10:35 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:18:"Community Projects";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"General";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"Team";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"WordCamp";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"WordPress";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:16:"WordPress Meetup";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"http://webdevstudios.com/?p=8010";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:427:"This year for WordCamp Phoenix, Brad Williams, Lisa Sabin-Wilson, Brian Messenlehner, and Brad Parbs of WDS will be attending and speaking. WebDevStudios is also sponsoring this event! WCPHX is being held January 17-19, 2014 in Chandler, Arizona. Brad Parbs will be &#8230; <a class="more-link" href="http://webdevstudios.com/2014/01/15/wds-at-wordcamp-phoenix-2014/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Melissa Hoppe";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3390:"<p>This year for <a href="http://2014.phoenix.wordcamp.org/">WordCamp Phoenix,</a> <a title="Brad Williams" href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/brad-williams/">Brad Williams</a>, <a title="Lisa Sabin-Wilson" href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/lisa-sabin-wilson/">Lisa Sabin-Wilson</a>, <a title="Brian Messenlehner" href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/brian-messenlehner/">Brian Messenlehner</a>, and <a title="Brad Parbs" href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/brad-parbs/">Brad Parbs</a> of WDS will be attending and speaking. WebDevStudios is also sponsoring this event! WCPHX is being held January 17-19, 2014 in Chandler, Arizona.</p>\n<p><a href="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Screenshot_on_1.14.2014_at_10.50.48_AM.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-8012" alt="Screenshot_on_1.14.2014_at_10.50.48_AM" src="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Screenshot_on_1.14.2014_at_10.50.48_AM.png" width="946" height="246" /></a></p>\n<p><a title="Brad Parbs" href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/brad-parbs/">Brad Parbs</a> will be speaking on <strong>Friday January 17th, at 9AM in the Advanced Dev Track</strong>. His presentation will tell you all about <span style="text-decoration: underline">Writing Extensible Plugins.</span></p>\n<p>Description:</p>\n<blockquote><p>Functionality in a WordPress site usually requires a variety of plugins, all that need to work together. Sometimes, plugins need to be extended and modified. We’ll go through how to build a plugin that supports extensibility and modification, without hacks. This will be an interactive session, where everyone can share their tips and tricks for this.</p></blockquote>\n<p><a title="Brad Williams" href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/brad-williams/">Brad Williams</a> will be speaking at <strong>3:15PM Saturday January 18th in the Extension &amp; Development track. </strong>He will be telling you all about <span style="text-decoration: underline">Writing Secure WordPress Code</span>.</p>\n<p>Description:</p>\n<blockquote><p>You’ll learn the proper way to write the most secure code in WordPress. Whether you’re a plugin developer or build themes, it’s extremely important to understand how to secure your code from hacks and exploits. Overlooking some very easy to follow techniques can expose your website to the hackers everywhere. WordPress features a number of built-in methods to help make sure your code is safe and secure, and we’ll cover each and every one in detail.</p></blockquote>\n<p>Brian and Lisa will not be speaking at this event, but will be in attendance in the crowd. If you see any of them, make sure stop and say hi!</p>\n<p>If you don&#8217;t get the chance to speak with Brad, Brian, Lisa, or Brad P. during WordCamp hours, you can catch them all at the after events including &#8212; <a href="http://2014.phoenix.wordcamp.org/session/wine-and-design-happy-hour-awards/">Wine and Design Happy Hour &amp; Awards</a>, <a href="http://2014.phoenix.wordcamp.org/session/speakers-organizers-and-sponsors-dinner/">Speakers, Organizers, and Sponsors Dinner</a>, and the <a href="http://2014.phoenix.wordcamp.org/session/afterparty-at-chandler-city-hall/">After Party at Chandler City Hall</a>! They all look forward to seeing everyone they&#8217;ve already met and getting to meet new people who have the same passion for WordPress as they do.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:70:"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/01/15/wds