(2370, 299, 'new_paragraph_9_new_content', 'The story of John E. Brownlee is as much about progressive thinking and innovation as it is about passion and dedication. Not only did he establish one of Alberta''s most successful law practices, he served two terms as Premier of Alberta, he created and shaped the cooperative movement and the creation of member cooperatives across Western Canada, he created and ultimately led the United Grain Growers, and he ultimately foresaw that the future of Alberta and Albertans lay in the resource wealth that ought to belong to all of its citizens. It is not an exaggeration to state that much of the prosperity that Alberta enjoys today can be traced back to the vision that Mr. Brownlee had for Alberta both during and well after he held public office. His vision is one of the legacies that still lives within the walls of Brownlee LLP, the firm which proudly bears Mr. Brownlee''s name.'),
(2371, 299, '_new_paragraph_9_new_content', 'field_531d701b6e41a'),
(2372, 299, 'new_paragraph_10_new_title', 'Notable Brownlee LLP Appointments'),
(2373, 299, '_new_paragraph_10_new_title', 'field_531d6fe36e419'),
(2374, 299, 'new_paragraph_10_new_content', 'Several Brownlee LLP lawyers have received judicial appointments, including Ernest J. Walter, Q.C., now a Judge of the Provincial Court of Alberta and formerly Chief Judge of the Provincial Court of Alberta; Peter T. Costigan, Q.C. formerly a Justice of the Court of Queen''s Bench of Alberta, now a Justice of the Court of Appeal of Alberta; Paul G. Sully, Q.C., appointed a Judge of the Provincial Court of Alberta; Leo J. Burgess, Q.C., appointed a Judge in the Provincial Court of Alberta; and Bruce R. Garriock, Q.C., appointed a Judge in the Provincial Court of Alberta. Many Brownlee LLP lawyers have written scholarly articles on various aspects of the law, and have fulfilled speaking engagements on legal subjects.  Read more about these by clicking on events and legal information resources.\r\nTo discover the scope of legal services we offer, click on practice areas.  To learn more about the individual lawyers and the area of their legal expertise, please click on lawyers.  To read our wide range of articles, publications and other legal materials, please click on legal information resources.  To find out how to contact us, and to become more familiar with our firm, click on about us.'),
(2375, 299, '_new_paragraph_10_new_content', 'field_531d701b6e41a'),
(2376, 299, 'new_paragraph_11_new_title', 'Municipal Helpline'),
(2377, 299, '_new_paragraph_11_new_title', 'field_531d6fe36e419'),
(2378, 299, 'new_paragraph_11_new_content', 'Brownlee LLP is pleased to offer its Municipal Helpline service as part of its continued commitment to municipalities, and the people that make them better.\r\n\r\nAs a result of decades of commitment to the needs of municipalities, we understand that brief discussions of legal issues can often avoid costly discussion, conflict and litigation later on. Through this continuous dedication to local issues, the Municipal Helpline has developed into an indispensable value-added service that is made available with no strings attached. It offers risk management through sound consultation and guidance, based upon unparalleled experience, resulting in risk avoidance. It defines what we call the "municipal relationship."'),
