(5367, 421, 'bio', 'Derek is the Leader of the Firm''s Municipal Enforcement Group and Environmental Law Practice. In the Environmental sphere, Derek has extensive experience in the defence of environmental prosecutions and regulatory processes, advising organizations and operational staff training investigations and inspections, the provision of proactive advice respecting environmental management and planning, advising organizations on regulatory compliance, providing environmental due diligence and risk assessment in support of commercial transactions and representing clients before various appeal bodies, including the Alberta Environmental Appeals Board. Additionally, in the area of Water Law, Derek has extensive experience in the areas of water acquisition, allocations and transfers, protection of potable water supplies, preservation of water rights and regulatory issues associated with fisheries and fish habitat.\r\n\r\nIn the area of Municipal Enforcement, Derek has significant experience in a broad spectrum of Municipal Enforcement Issues including Planning and Development, Nuisance and Unsightly Properties, Safety Code compliance, Tax Recovery, Emergency Services Liability, Expropriations, Bylaw Prosecutions and Injunctive Enforcement under the Municipal Government Act.\r\n\r\nDerek has appeared before all levels of Court in Alberta and has represented client interests before various statutory tribunals including the Environmental Appeal Board, Safety Codes Council and Local Planning boards.'),
