(5956, 451, 'bio', 'Colin’s practice focuses as a first priority on assisting employers with pro-active employee management to avoid pitfalls and manage risk in all facets of an employer’s Human Resources activities.  When proceeding to litigation, arbitration or a hearing is necessary, Colin has an enviable track record of success before all levels of the Courts of Alberta, numerous Employment and Labour Related tribunals, as well as a successful appearance at the Supreme Court of Canada.\r\n\r\nColin acts as counsel for employers across Alberta, the Northwest Territories, and Nunavut before all levels of the Courts, Human Rights Commissions, Labour Relations Boards, Grievance Arbitrators, Boards of Reference, Employment Standards, and Occupational Health and Safety.  His primary practice area is management side Labour &amp; Employment for both unionized and non-unionized work environments.\r\n\r\nColin regularly advises and represents a wide variety of employers, ranging from large national companies through to small business and charitable community organizations.  In particular, Colin has extensive experience and specialization in the representation of Municipal and School Division clients, and in these areas his practice and experience also extends to a wide array of issues affecting these unique institutional clients such as governance, risk management, and other issues arising from legislation such as the School Act and Municipal Government Act.\r\n\r\nColin’s work includes a wide breadth of services including proactive legal advice regarding issues such as hiring, discipline, termination; the duty to accommodate; contract and policy development and review; collective bargaining; grievances and arbitrations; Boards of Reference; wrongful dismissal litigation; workplace reorganizations; negotiating severance and retirement packages; Human Rights complaints; confidentiality, non-competition and non-solicitation agreements; workplace drug and alcohol testing; employee training and development agreements; Alberta and Canada Employment Standards Code Complaints; and independent contractor agreements.'),
(5957, 451, '_bio', 'field_5323822abc024'),
(5958, 451, 'representative_work', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Colin has extensive specialization in the representation of Municipal and School Division clients, and focuses on Proactive Employee Management;</li>\r\n	<li>Colin was successful Counsel for the Intervener, the Alberta Urban Municipalities Association, at the Supreme Court of Canada in the case of Her Majesty The Queen v. Public Service Alliance of Canada;</li>\r\n	<li>Colin was successful Counsel in landmark School Boundary Case (Calgary Board of Education v. Palliser Regional Division No. 26)</li>\r\n</ul>');
