(6508, 475, 'bio', 'Steve acts as counsel for employers across Alberta before all levels of the Courts, the Alberta Human Rights Commission, the Canadian Human Rights Commission, the Canadian Human Rights Tribunal, and the Alberta Labour Relations Board. His primary practice area is in Labour &amp; Employment from a management perspective for both unionized and non-unionized work environments. He has considerable experience in related areas including Education, Human Rights, Occupational Health and Safety, Privacy and Access to Information, among others. Steve also acts for many Nunavut and Northwest Territories municipal clients in the field of Labour and Employment Law.\r\n\r\nSteve has developed extensive specialization in the representation of municipal clients, seniors'' housing, school divisions, EMS providers as well as private corporations and non-profit organizations of all sizes. He provides a focus on proactive employee management to assist employers in avoiding pitfalls and managing risk so that they can achieve their core business goals.\r\n\r\nHis work includes a wide breadth of services including proactive legal advice regarding issues such as hiring, discipline, termination and accommodation; contract and policy development and review; collective bargaining; grievances and arbitrations; Boards of Reference; wrongful dismissal litigation; workplace reorganizations; negotiating severance and retirement packages; managing human rights; confidentiality, non-competition and non-solicitation agreements; workplace drug and alcohol testing; employee training and development agreements; Alberta Employment Standards Code Complaints and Canada Labour Code Complaints; independent contractor agreements; obligations to and risk-management of volunteers; and others.'),
(6509, 475, '_bio', 'field_5323822abc024'),
(6510, 475, 'representative_work', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Focuses on a proactive approach to workplace management to support employers as they pursue their core business objectives, and to manage risk and reduce exposure to liability.</li>\r\n	<li>Provides advice on all aspects of managing unionized work environments including collective bargaining, grievances, arbitrations, and classification issues.</li>\r\n	<li>Provides advice on all aspects of managing non-unionized work environments including policy and contract development; guidance regarding hiring, discipline and termination; Employment Standards and Canada Labour Code complaints.</li>\r\n</ul>'),
(6511, 475, '_representative_work', 'field_532382ccbc029'),
(6512, 475, 'memberships', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Member, Canadian Bar Association, Education Law Subsection</li>\r\n	<li>Member, Canadian Bar Association, Labour &amp; Employment Law Subsection</li>\r\n</ul>'),
